  "description": "Torus T(5,2) — a higher-order ratio that creates more complex delay length relationships than T(3,2). At 2.2 Hz pulse with low entrainment (0.3), the exotic ratio produces trigger-like articulations that feel melodic but rhythmically irregular. Square LFO hard-gates the filter for additional punch.",
